        <div class="recipe" id="pancakes">
            <h2>Fluffy Pancakes</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Time: 20 minutes</li>
                <li>Serves: 4</li>
            </ul>

            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Ingredient</th>
                        <th>Quantity</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Flour</td>
                        <td>1 cup</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Sugar</td>
                        <td>2 tbsp</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Milk</td>
                        <td>1 cup</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Egg</td>
                        <td>1 large</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>

            <p><strong>Steps:</strong></p>
            <ol>
                <li>In a bowl, mix flour, sugar, and a pinch of salt.</li>
                <li>Add milk and whisk until smooth.</li>
                <li>Heat a non-stick pan and pour batter to form small pancakes.</li>
                <li>Cook until bubbles form, then flip and cook the other side.</li>
                <li>Serve warm with syrup and butter.</li>
            </ol>

            <p><em>Source: <a href="https://www.allrecipes.com/">AllRecipes</a></em></p>
        </div>

        <div class="recipe" id="spaghetti">
            <h2>Classic Spaghetti</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Time: 30 minutes</li>
                <li>Serves: 4</li>
            </ul>

            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Ingredient</th>
                        <th>Quantity</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Spaghetti</td>
                        <td>500g</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Tomato Sauce</td>
                        <td>2 cups</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Ground Beef</td>
                        <td>250g</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Garlic</td>
                        <td>2 cloves</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>

            <p><strong>Steps:</strong></p>
            <ol>
                <li>Boil spaghetti in salted water until al dente.</li>
                <li>In a pan, cook ground beef until browned.</li>
                <li>Add garlic and tomato sauce to the beef and simmer for 10 minutes.</li>
                <li>Drain spaghetti and mix with the sauce.</li>
                <li>Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.</li>
            </ol>

            <p><em>Source: <a href="https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/">BBC Good Food</a></em></p>
        </div>
